cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SY 

This paper discusses the impact of Internet eXchange Points (IXPs) on interdomain connectivity and the shaping of the current Internet. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also touches upon security and privacy concerns related to IXPs, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. Additionally, the paper uses data analysis and modeling techniques to understand the impact of IXPs, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category. The paper also discusses the impact of IXPs on the hierarchy of the Internet, which could place it in the cs.CY (Computers and Society) category. Finally, the paper discusses the role of IXPs in enabling interdomain connectivity, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category.
